        "richtext_h9pFRM": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>In the glass, Maniére Noire Champagne ($125 USD) reveals a brilliant salmon-pink hue with copper reflections and a delicate stream of fine bubbles. The aroma opens with wild strawberry, raspberry, and redcurrant, layered with soft notes of cherry and cream. On the palate, it is vibrant and rounded — its sweetness lifted by clean acidity, its finish long and resonant. Every detail reflects craftsmanship, patience, and a dedication to excellence that defines A Ma Maniére’s world.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_8tpcmT": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
